instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The DT lifecycle begins with the creation of system models that capture both the physical and cyber aspects of the asset. During deployment, these models are integrated into the DT framework. Continuous calibration algorithms update model parameters using real‑time sensor data, ensuring that the virtual representation remains faithful to the physical twin. Runtime monitoring processes the updated models and sensor streams to identify safety or performance violations. When such violations are detected, either human operators or autonomous supervisory algorithms initiate corrective actions that feed back into the system, completing the lifecycle loop and enabling ongoing refinement."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The DT’s fidelity is ensured through continuous calibration: model parameters are refined using incoming sensor data to minimise discrepancies between simulation and reality. Validation is performed by monitors that compare operational metrics against predefined safety and performance constraints; fault detectors flag deviations. State estimators infer unmeasured states, while optimisers evaluate alternative control actions based on the calibrated models. This closed‑loop data–model–control cycle underpins the DT’s capacity to detect, correct, and prevent faults, thereby maintaining confidence in both the models and the data streams."
]
